         It blows my mind that people can still give Verant the benefit of the doubt.  Its just as boggling that people would discount test server data.  Yes its true that they *could* alter our spell list right before the release, but its much more likely that what is on the test server now is what is going to make it to the live servers.  Its October already.  PoP is going to be released come hell or high water in less than three weeks now, with each passing day it becomes more and more likely that we are going to be stuck with the dung heap we got now for PoP Spells and new AA abilities.</P><P>The time to point out the obvious to clueless Verant folks is NOW.  History has shown that they are very slow to make changes after an expansion unless its a nerf.</P><P>It doesnt take a genius to see:</P><P>1) The PoP AA abilities suck for the most part.  Pet FD?  LOL come on.  Improved healing for taps?  Uh, no thanks.  And finally, my favorite, improved refresh time for our shit AE undead only mez.  Thanks for not even bothering to play our class prior to creating new AA abilities for us guys.</P><P>2) The new DoTs suck for the most part.  They arent covered by level 3 focus items, and FP beats them all overall.  The efficiency of most of the new DoTs is shit (some DDs are better! WHAT THE FUCK!?!?!?).  The damage is shit.  Mobs get more and more HPs, all the other DPS classes get more and more DPS.  We get...uh, still waiting.  The resists on poison arent as good for us as FP.</P><P>3) Pets.  The jury is out on this one, but based on Kunark pets, dont hold your breath.  EoT sucked for well over a year.  A YEAR.</P><P>4) Focus effects.  Touched on this above, but the fact that our necro book doesnt affect 60+ pets, and level 3 focus items dont work on 61 and up spells sucks, bad.</P><P>Sayleth</P><P>And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death - Revelation 6:8</P><P>Edited by - Sayleth on 10/03/2002  13:23:47<a href="#top"><img src="icon_